1
00:00:05,191 --> 00:00:06,645
This is what 
Guru Mahārāj says

2
00:00:06,645 --> 00:00:09,210
about taking a stand
with spiritual common sense.

3
00:00:09,210 --> 00:00:13,037
I can sit here, we can quote
so many scriptures, verses, etc.

4
00:00:13,268 --> 00:00:16,573
but also just use 
your common sense too.

5
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:21,142
[Is God Male, Female, or Both?]

6
00:00:26,081 --> 00:00:29,339
There’s another liker 
as we speak.

7
00:00:30,658 --> 00:00:35,823
You see how relationship 
driven we are in this world,

8
00:00:36,340 --> 00:00:38,123
learn from it!

9
00:00:38,508 --> 00:00:40,651
It must be there
in the original.

10
00:00:41,113 --> 00:00:44,688
This is the driving principle 
of existence,

11
00:00:45,514 --> 00:00:52,058
so to what degree is it accommodated
in theistic systems?

12
00:00:53,222 --> 00:01:01,830
So, for the most part, in religion
there’s a male God,

13
00:01:02,183 --> 00:01:09,252
and the feminine aspect is under-served,
under-represented,

14
00:01:09,467 --> 00:01:11,215
to put it mildly.

15
00:01:15,994 --> 00:01:18,754
Then, what do people think
to compensate for that?

16
00:01:18,847 --> 00:01:22,154
“Yes! So, we worship 
the Goddess!”

17
00:01:25,173 --> 00:01:28,394
Just to go
in the other direction.

18
00:01:31,249 --> 00:01:47,718
But the only fully balanced complete
expression of Divinity is in Bhagavān—

19
00:01:47,995 --> 00:01:50,925
meaning: Śakti−Śaktimān;

20
00:01:50,925 --> 00:01:55,476
feminine aspect
and male aspect;

21
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:59,566
the Supreme Female
and the Supreme Male.

